{"questionId":"16980","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">An object hangs from a light string and moves in a horizontal circle of radius <em>r</em>.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/2c16bd9ea7e5f93f6985c6d08f866a02e7d36da4.png\" width=\"194\" height=\"205\"></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">The string makes an angle <em>θ</em> with the vertical. The angular speed of the object is <em>ω</em>. What is tan <em>θ</em>?</span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>r</mi></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mrow><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mi>r</mi></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ω</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow><mi>g</mi></mfrac></math></span></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>g</mi><mrow><mi>ω</mi><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfrac></math></span></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"16980","referenceCode":"19N.1.SL.TZ0.21","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An object hangs from a light string and moves in a horizontal circle of radius r. The string makes an angle θ with the vertical. The angular speed of the object is ω. What is tan θ","paper":"1","level":"